syntax:
ssh user@ip -p[port if any]


------------------------------------------
SSH is secure shell which is use to logged in on other server 
SSH Client must be install on servers for this (openssh-server)

----------------------------------------------

sudo apt-get install openssh-server :will install ssh Client on system
ssh: will show if ssh is installed or not
ssh localhost   :will connect to localhost
sudo service ssh status :this will show the service is running for ssh
exit    :will close the connection to loggen in server i.e. localhost for our case